title: Dire Straits - Werchter Festival, Brussels, Belgium 1981-07-05
description:
Dire Straits - Brussels, Belgium, Werchter Festival - 1981-07-05

Unofficial soundboard recording - very high quality

recorded at the
Werchter Festival, 
Brussels, Belgium
5th July 1981



Tracklist:

01 Once upon a time in the west
02 Expresso love
03 Down to the waterline
04 Skateaway
05 Romeo and Juliet
06 News
07 Private investigations
08 Sultans of swing
09 Angel of mercy
10 Tunnel of love


Lineup:

Mark Knopfler - lead guitar, lead vocals
John Illsley - bass, vocals
Hal Lindes - guitar, vocals
Alan Clark - keyboards
Pick Withers - drums, vocals


Notes:

Tracks 1,3,4,6,7,9 & 10 recorded from radio broadcast in Werchter, Brussels, Belgium on July 5, 1981 - the same show released on the other bootlegs "News", "Before we became famous" and "Once Upon a Time"

tracks 2, 5 & 8 from different unofficial sources, probably recordings from the same period
